    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2019-10-24</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-01-27T17:44:47Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Integrated Energy Systems Act of 2019 </b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Energy to establish an integrated energy systems program to (1) maximize energy production and efficiency; (2) provide reliable, competitive, and environmentally sustainable electricity to the grid; (3) expand the use of emissions-reducing energy technologies into nonelectric sectors; and (4) enable U.S. energy infrastructure to support the quantity, variability in type, and variability in size of generation devices and smart load devices.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>25</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2019-12-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Reported to Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-03-10T18:32:10Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Integrated Energy Systems Act of 2019 </b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Energy (DOE) to establish an integrated energy systems program to (1) maximize energy production and efficiency; (2) develop energy systems involving the integration of nuclear energy with renewable energy, fossil energy, and energy storage; and (3) expand the use of emissions-reducing energy technologies into nonelectric sectors to achieve significant reductions in environmental emissions.</p> <p>DOE must establish quantitative goals and milestones for the program.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
